400
00:19:18,120 --> 00:19:20,440
to continue lensing flicks

401
00:19:20,440 --> 00:19:23,000
when we never seem to grow as visual storytellers

402
00:19:23,000 --> 00:19:25,560
or keep making, what's to them, the same movie.

403
00:19:25,560 --> 00:19:28,040
The answer is that we've never lost anybody money.

404
00:19:28,040 --> 00:19:29,080
I'll say that again.

405
00:19:29,080 --> 00:19:31,400
We've never lost anybody money.

406
00:19:31,400 --> 00:19:33,240
Granted, we came close with Rats,

407
00:19:33,240 --> 00:19:35,240
but even that made a killing on video

408
00:19:35,320 --> 00:19:37,640
and, more recently, DVD.

409
00:19:37,640 --> 00:19:39,320
Despite box office troubles,

410
00:19:39,320 --> 00:19:41,240
the same film no one went to see

411
00:19:41,240 --> 00:19:42,360
and critics snubbed

412
00:19:42,360 --> 00:19:44,280
was suddenly doing gangbusters,

413
00:19:44,280 --> 00:19:46,680
making it an even more interesting sort of cult hit

414
00:19:46,680 --> 00:19:47,800
than its predecessor,

415
00:19:47,800 --> 00:19:50,120
and it's because of the aesthetic differences

416
00:19:50,120 --> 00:19:51,640
of playing a film on a TV.

417
00:19:51,640 --> 00:19:53,240
All of a sudden, the shot composition

418
00:19:53,240 --> 00:19:54,040
isn't as important

419
00:19:54,040 --> 00:19:55,320
because it's kind of far away from you

420
00:19:55,320 --> 00:19:56,280
and you're doing something else

421
00:19:56,280 --> 00:19:57,400
in the room while it plays

422
00:19:57,400 --> 00:19:58,840
and the low quality of the format

423
00:19:58,840 --> 00:20:00,040
means that even if the shots

424
00:20:00,040 --> 00:20:01,080
were particularly good,

425
00:20:01,080 --> 00:20:02,760
you wouldn't really have noticed anyway.

426
00:20:02,760 --> 00:20:04,280
You aren't having the aimless banter

427
00:20:04,280 --> 00:20:05,560
about nothing blasted at you

428
00:20:05,560 --> 00:20:06,760
from speakers all around you

429
00:20:06,760 --> 00:20:08,520
like it's the most important thing in the world

430
00:20:08,520 --> 00:20:10,440
and you have to listen to every second.

431
00:20:10,440 --> 00:20:11,480
It's playing nearby

432
00:20:11,480 --> 00:20:12,760
and you're just kind of listening in

433
00:20:12,760 --> 00:20:14,600
on these people talking free associatively

434
00:20:14,600 --> 00:20:16,040
about their film opinions.

435
00:20:16,040 --> 00:20:18,200
With this change in the viewing experience,

436
00:20:18,200 --> 00:20:19,080
all of a sudden,

437
00:20:19,080 --> 00:20:20,760
More Rats makes sense.

438
00:20:20,760 --> 00:20:22,200
It becomes a funny little film

439
00:20:22,200 --> 00:20:23,800
where the big scenes and funnier jokes

440
00:20:23,800 --> 00:20:24,600
grab your attention

441
00:20:24,600 --> 00:20:25,640
and the stuff that falls flat

442
00:20:25,640 --> 00:20:26,760
or isn't so well-directed

443
00:20:26,760 --> 00:20:27,640
doesn't matter so much

444
00:20:27,640 --> 00:20:29,080
because it's easier to ignore.

445
00:20:29,080 --> 00:20:31,560
Here's an IMDb review from 2003.

446
00:20:31,560 --> 00:20:34,200
Brad C-2 from Auckland, New Zealand

447
00:20:34,200 --> 00:20:35,800
